SUMMARY:Adopting GitHub in the Enterprise: Best Practices and Strategies
DESCRIPTION:Toronto Enterprise DevOps User Group\nAdopting GitHub in an en
 terprise environment can significantly enhance collaboration\, streamline 
 workflows\, and improve code quality. However\, successful adoption requir
 es careful planning and implementation of best practices. This presentatio
 n will cover key strategies for integrating GitHub into your organization'
 s development processes. We will discuss topics such as setting up reposit
 ories\, managing access controls\, implementing branching strategies\, and
  leveraging GitHub Actions for CI/CD. Additionally\, we will explore how t
 o foster a culture of collaboration through code reviews and issue trackin
 g. Attendees will gain insights into overcoming common challenges and ensu
 ring a smooth transition to GitHub\, ultimately driving productivity and i
 nnovation within their teams.\n\nKey topics covered:\n\n* Setting up singl
 e sign-on (SSO) and integrating with existing identity providers\n* Config
 uring Enterprise Account settings and policies\n* Organization structure a
 nd repository management\n* Managing user access and permissions effective
 ly\n* Hybrid Model for GitHub and Azure DevOps\n* Securing GitHub Actions 
 and workflows\n* Implementing shift-left security practices\n* Addressing 
 security concerns and ensuring data protection\n* Rolling out GitHub Copil
 ot in an enterprise setting\n* Leveraging GitHub Apps and integrations for
  enhanced functionality\n* Integrating GitHub with existing development to
 ols and systems\n* Monitoring and auditing usage for compliance\n\n*Come a
 t 5:30 pm have some pizza and chat for a bit. The presentation starts at 6
 :00 pm.*
